Package net.marfgamer.jraknet.server

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    RakNetServerListener
    This interface is used by the server to let the user know when specific events are triggered

    Note: Do NOT use Thread.sleep(long) in any of these methods, as it will cause the server to timeout!
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BlockedClient
    This class represents an address that the server has blocked and stores how much time until they are unblocked
    RakNetServer
    This class is used to easily create servers using the RakNet protocol
    RakNetServerHandler
    This class is instantiated by the server with the sole purpose of sending received packets to the server so they can be properly handled
    ServerPing
    Used primarily to box an identifier sent in the response of a server to a ping sent by a client (Or maybe another server? :O) so it can be modified by the user
